Community members in Alexandra are held a safety summit in an effort to reclaim their streets. Residents say they are tired of the high levels of crime in the area. They also accuse the police of brutality. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The community of Alexandra, north of Johannesburg, says it has very little faith in police eradicating crime in the area. Gauteng Community Safety MEC Faith Mazibuko visited the area on Saturday to engage with residents about the way forward. READ: Ipid probes fatal shooting of Alexandra mom Police and community members spent the day trying to find solutions to the high crime rate in the area. For some residents - trusting the police is a no-no but police say community members must come forward with proof of their claims and not allow criminals to come between them and solving crime.